Pokemon experience:
https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Experience

For my create your own assignment:
I added a catch rate taken from https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Catch_rate in the generation
II and beyond section. To do this I had to use the pokemon species data file that contains the
capture rate for each pokemon_id. I also, had it only use pokemon whose id was less than or equal
to 898 because the bigger ones don't have a capture rate, and I also just don't like them very much.
I also added that a user can have up to 12 pokemon total. They can switch out these pokemon by entering
a pokemon center. There they can add up to 6 pokemon to their party. They can also transfer pokemon.
This allows the user to get rid of pokemon so they can catch more after they have hit the 12 pokemon.
Once a pokemon is transfered, it is gone, and they will not be able to get it back.

I also added XP for pokemon. Each pokemon starts with the experience it needs to have for its level
based on experience.csv. Your pokemon then earn experience points every time they knock out a pokemon
whether in a wild pokemon battle or a trainer battle. This experience is calculated based on the flat
formula for generations I - IV as described in https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Experience. This
experience is then split between each of the pokemon in the party that are not kncoked out. When
a pokemon levels up, their stats all level up with them. When the PC goes to the pokemon center, they
also have a choice see new moves for their pokemon. This page asks them to pick from one of their pokemon.
Then if they have any moves that are unlocked at the level they are on, the pokemon center will display
them. If the player wants, they can choose to learn one of the new moves. In order to do this they will be
asked to forget one of their current two moves. This allows pokemon to level up and unlock better moves
as they do so.